verbose_text: In the hypothyroidism group, plasma irisin levels were positively associated with FT3 (r = 0.239, P = 0.036) and FT4 levels (r = 0.456, P < 0.001), and negatively associated with CHOL (r = -0.429, P < 0.001), LDL-C (r = -0.383, P = 0.001), TG (r = -0.284, P = 0.012), and TSH levels (r = -0.408, P < 0.001).
